So yummy! We sampled all the Onigiri. The pork and the pickled plum are especially scrumptious, but they were all amazing. The staff is kind and friendly as well.

Matcha fanatic here! This place has the best matcha I’ve ever had. They use extremely high quality ingredients, and have a subtle hint of white chocolate in their matcha. It’s absolutely delicious and worth coming out of your way for!
Disappointingly weak coffee.  There may be other itmes to try here.

I can't even let myself go into detail about how much I love this coffee shop. I would end up writing a multi page essay. Everything about this place is honestly perfect for my taste in cafe establishments. The coffee is great, they actually steam the milk when you order milk in just a normal cup of coffee. Beans are affordable and good. The music they play are some of my favorite styles. The food is unreal, and priced well for what you get. The Onigiri are a great snack. The location aesthetically and architecturally is dope! And the staff pretty much get the chillest and coolest in East Williamsburg award. I have yet to try their non coffee drinks, save for tea of which they have a great selection. Lastly, this place actually had a hand in our criteria to move into this neighborhood. We legit loved it so much it was on our pros for reasons we wanted to live nearby. It has great energy and community. Highly recommend.
mmm this cafe is my fav in the city. coffee is always delicious, and they always steam your milk, even if it's just to pour over a regular coffee!
Best coffee in the neighborhood.

i really wanted to give this place more stars because their matcha is     a m a z i n g   and almost makes everything worth it, but the times i have gotten food there it has been quite disappointing. Their salmon bento is kinda like the ones you can get for 300 yen at family mart in japan, except here you can get it for about $15. Their pork onigiri was okay (rice was dry), but the salmon one had an insulting amount of salmon (literally the size of my fingertip). Also the staff come off as either rude or indifferent, makes you feel kinda like a nuisance.

One of my favorite places in NYC. The coffee is exceptional, the croissants are perfectly flakey, the people are kind, the music is inspired. If I lived here, I would spend all my money at Brooklyn Ball Factory. I can’t recommend this place enough!!

I leave in the neighborhood for 13 years and actually like the place and people there are very nice but after going there for few years I will stop, today I took for the first time the vegan curry and this was the cherry on the cake, the portions are so small, (I am a skinny guy and don’t eat like a big football player) so I paid $14 for basically a curry sauce next to a small bowl or rice and a bit of salad , ok it’s good (for everyday basic lunch, nothing whaou) but what would it cost them to put a bit more rice in the box??? I go to all the restaurants they have and was one of the first to go to samurai mama from day 1as I knew the managers from Bozu. If you wanna eat there just make sure you not too hungry.

The menu's hanging at the "wrongest" place possible - right next to the customers' faces and table while they were eating and chatting. No printouts for the menu either and there's not enough space to have your meal. Food's good though, but what's the point when every thing else isn't.  and to make it worst, the cash register (the girl) was so rude to customers, telling us that we are too lazy to look at the menu (overheard her talking to fellow employees in her native language) You can tell me that when u get urselves some printouts 'kay?! You weren't helpful either *psht*  So NO, will not recommend this place to anyone new coming in.

Absolutely fantastic - Review update time pitches! Super good clean tasting food. Not cheap, but reasonable prices. Hip atmosphere with a roof deck. Night time has a bigger menu. I had a dark udon noodle that was the bomb. Lots of good vibes.

I love this place! I come all the time for a quick pick me up of onigiri rice balls. I've tried the chashu and the salmon and they are both fantastic. The hoji latte is also really good, a little on the sweet side, but I'm sure it could be adjusted. Their bentos are delicious as well. The cafe is not the most comfortable to sit in, but it's good enough. It's also nice that they stay  open late and you can have your laptop and do work. When it's warmer in the spring or summer I'd love to come back and enjoy their patio area!
Coffee was $4 and... smaller than expected. The rooftop is very nice and so are all of the staff, and the food is very good as well. Overall, I'd recommend for a quick bite but not much else.

I only can review the matcha latte. It was good but def on the sweeter side. I like sweet, but this a little too sweet. Maybe ask them to give less sugar next time. It is a very cute place though.

Absolutely love me some health food at times and Brooklyn Ball serves exactly that.  Firstly, walking in, you're greeted by the fresh smell of Japanese cuisine cooking and all you want to do is order the entire menu to boast to everyone that you've been eating healthy for a day.  I usually order the grilled salmon bento box for lunch. It includes some edemame, grilled veggies and delicious rice. On occasion I order the grilled salmon on a ciabatta! And holy damn, that sandwich is super tasteful and filling.  They have delicious fresh brewed coffees and amazing teas, all at very reasonable prices.  They have an awesome outdoor seating space including indoor seating. Everything about this place is spot on and I'm in love that it's steps from my office!  If you're looking for healthy, filling and super delicious foods, this is your place.
Great little coffee shop, yummy bentonite boxes, and a cozy rooftop

What an amazing find. The cafes around here are unassuming. Hidden behind a large metal door you will find the most coolest hipster Japanese cafe. The vibe is trendy with earthy tones and bright open spaces. The menu contains a good selection of Japanese staples including Bento Boxes. They also specialise in excellent coffee made either espresso style or cold drip. Not to be missed is their absolutely delicious iced matcha, yum! The bento was a great lunch, not the biggest portion but enough for lunch. There is also a rooftop deck which would be great on a later summers day with a beverage in hand.
